ned inrush from tripping shared BMS overcurrent protection#{8}":[52,52],"#staggered motor startup by 100ms prevents combined inrush from tripping shared BMS overcurrent protection#{9}":[53,53],"#staggered motor startup by 100ms prevents combined inrush from tripping shared BMS overcurrent protection#{10}":[54,54],"#staggered motor startup by 100ms prevents combined inrush from tripping shared BMS overcurrent protection#{11}":[55,56],"#staggered motor startup by 100ms prevents combined inrush from tripping shared BMS overcurrent protection#{12}":[57,57],"#staggered motor startup by 100ms prevents combined inrush from tripping shared BMS overcurrent protection#{13}":[58,58],"#staggered motor startup by 100ms prevents combined inrush from tripping shared BMS overcurrent protection#{14}":[59,59],"#staggered motor startup by 100ms prevents combined inrush from tripping shared BMS overcurrent protection#{15}":[60,61]},"outlinks":[{"title":"actuators","target":"actuators","line":7},{"title":"power-systems","target":"power-systems","line":8},{"title":"eda-fundamentals","target":"eda-fundamentals","line":9},{"title":"bms-discharge-port-is-the-sole-power-output-so-a-bms-trip-kills-the-mcu-along-with-the-motors","target":"bms-discharge-port-is-the-sole-power-output-so-a-bms-trip-kills-the-mcu-along-with-the-motors","line":14},{"title":"four-motor-bldc-systems-exceed-standard-hoverboard-bms-ratings-requiring-firmware-current-limiting","target":"four-motor-bldc-systems-exceed-standard-hoverboard-bms-ratings-requiring-firmware-current-limiting","line":26},{"title":"wiring-dual-zs-x11h-for-hoverboard-robot","target":"wiring-dual-zs-x11h-for-hoverboard-robot","line":49},{"title":"four-motor-bldc-systems-exceed-standard-hoverboard-bms-ratings-requiring-firmware-current-limiting","target":"four-motor-bldc-systems-exceed-standard-hoverboard-bms-ratings-requiring-firmware-current-limiting","line":52},{"title":"bms-discharge-port-is-the-sole-power-output-so-a-bms-trip-kills-the-mcu-along-with-the-motors","target":"bms-discharge-port-is-the-sole-power-output-so-a-bms-trip-kills-the-mcu-along-with-the-motors","line":53},{"title":"neopixel-rings-need-a-bulk-electrolytic-capacitor-across-power-to-absorb-inrush-current","target":"neopixel-rings-need-a-bulk-electrolytic-capacitor-across-power-to-absorb-inrush-current","line":54},{"title":"tank-steering-replaces-mechanical-steering-with-differential-wheel-speed-control","target":"tank-steering-replaces-mechanical-steering-with-differential-wheel-speed-control","line":55},{"title":"actuators","target":"actuators","line":58},{"title":"power-systems","target":"power-systems","line":59},{"title":"eda-fundamentals","target":"eda-fundamentals","line":60}],"metadata":{"description":"Two or more motors accelerating simultaneously from a single battery stack up their inrush currents, often exceeding the BMS trip point even when each individual motor stays within its limit — offsetting motor start commands by 100ms spreads the inrush peaks in time, keeping instantaneous current below the trip threshold without requiring current sensing hardware","type":"claim","source":"docs/parts/wiring-dual-zs-x11h-for-hoverboard-robot.md","confidence":"proven","topics":["[[actuators]]","[[power-systems]]","[[eda-fundamentals]]"]},"task_lines":[],"tasks":{},"codeblock_ranges":[[18,22],[39,42]]},